job_text:
We are building a real(near)-time monitoring system that needs to track the activities of workers on a factory floor using video cameras. The goal of monitoring activities is to measure efficiency and ensure the safety of the workers on the factory floor.

Currently, we have 30+ cameras installed in various locations on the factory floor and the video streams are accessible via RSTP streams.

We are seeking someone that can help design the underlying architecture, lead the development effort, and guide in-house engineers.

An ideal candidate should have worked on such large-scale projects, has experience leading small-medium teams, and is experienced in building end-to-end computer vision pipelines.
